---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 110
By: St Augustine
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Illusion=The Consummation of Desire
  - Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin
---
He that perversely desires a good of nature, though he attain it, is evil
himself in the enjoyment of this good, and wretched, being deprived of a
better.
